<section class="page-section" id="A Call to action">
<h2><Center>A call to action</h2>
<body text="#00FFFD"
<table><center>
<table border=1>
<td><font size=4>	To break the generational cycles of lacking opportunity must start with the youth. America needs to do a much better job of providing children of all different backgrounds with a good start into life. We need schooling across low income areas to be improved to lower dropout rates and provide kids with better opportunities post high school. On top of this we need better community guidance to help kids stay with their families and away from child services. I also think the country could greatly benefit from a modified version of the affirmative action we saw in the past. However I think it should not be strictly based on race but a mixture of traits. Things such as where someone grew up, their economic status and that of their parents. I think this will help limit social unrest and provide the best net gain to the country as a whole. No child who is capable of reaching college should be held back because of the situation he was born into no matter what their race. After youth there also must be changes for adults in america. Companies should continue to try and diversify their business and not just for equality purposes but also for their own benefit. A solution is unlikely to ever be perfect but right now America is not doing enough. Kids who are unlucky enough to be born into a poor situation need to be helped. It will not just help them either. Who knows how many bright kids have gone down the wrong path due to limited resources. Increasing diversity will not just help minorities but the country as a whole. </td>
</table>
</section>
